sections.title: Basics of Python
sections.description: In this section, I learned the fundamentals of Python, including variables, data types, loops, and functions. These concepts are essential for writing clean and efficient code, which is critical for implementing AI algorithms.
takeaways: Learned how to write reusable functions.

sections.title: Strings
sections.description: In this section, I explored string manipulation techniques, including slicing, formatting, and built-in string methods. Understanding strings is crucial for working with text data in AI applications.
takeaways: Learned how to manipulate strings effectively.
Understood the importance of string formatting in AI workflows.

sections.title: Lists and List Comprehensions
sections.description: This section covers lists, a fundamental data structure in Python. I also learned about list comprehensions, which provide a concise way to create and manipulate lists.
takeaways: Mastered list operations such as appending, removing, and sorting.
Learned to use list comprehensions for cleaner code.

sections.title: Dictionaries
sections.description: Dictionaries are key-value pairs used to store and retrieve data efficiently. This section explores their usage and common operations.
takeaways: Learned how to access and modify dictionary values.

sections.title: NumPy for Numerical Computing
sections.description: NumPy is a powerful library for numerical computing in Python. This section introduces arrays, matrix operations, and other NumPy features.
takeaways: Learned how to create and manipulate NumPy arrays.
Understood the concept of broadcasting in NumPy.

sections.title: Pandas for Data Analysis
sections.description: Pandas is a library for data manipulation and analysis. This section covers DataFrames, data cleaning, and basic statistical operations.
takeaways: Learned how to load and manipulate data using Pandas.

sections.title: Matplotlib for Data Visualization
sections.description: Matplotlib is a plotting library for creating static, animated, and interactive visualizations. This section covers line plots, bar charts, and scatter plots.
takeaways: Learned how to create various types of plots.
Understood how to customize plot styles and labels.

sections.title: Scikit-learn for Machine Learning
sections.description: Scikit-learn is a library for machine learning in Python. This section introduces supervised and unsupervised learning algorithms.
takeaways: Learned how to train and evaluate machine learning models.
Explored classification, regression, and clustering algorithms.
